Why we need an Automated CRM Application?
Automating your CRM significantly reduces the time spent by sales teams on redundant sales activities such as 
data entry, data updates, call logs, and sending emails and follow-ups. CRM automation boosts productivity by saving this time and effort. 



What is Salesforce?
Salesforce creates and supports customer relationship management (CRM) software that helps break down the technology silos between departments 
to give companies a complete view of their customer everywhere they interact with your brand.



Types of salesforce applications?
Salesforce apps come in two flavors: Classic and Lightning. Classic apps are created and managed in Salesforce Classic. 
Lightning apps are created and managed in Lightning Experience. You can customize both types of app to match the way your users work.



